decipher (“rotate by 13 places”) is a special case of the Ceaser cipher in which the shift is always 13.
So every letter is shifted 13 places to encrypt or to decrypt the message.

Given a non-empty string like "PbQr" return a string like "CODE".

Q H P X
| | | |
D U C K


decipher('PbQr') → "CODE"
decipher("terljuvgr") → "GREYWHITE"
decipher("&nysn@") → "&Alfa@"